{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-10-07T11:53+0000", "md5": "1BAA346A92457D342C94B7D58F4764B4", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "HydroRoot", "normalizedForm": "HydroRoot", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 9}, "context": "HydroRoot uses a MTG (Godin and Caraglio, 1998) to represent root hydraulic architecture, which consists of the topology of a root system (branching positions, root lengths, root radii, etc.) and its hydraulic structure (local radial and axial conductivities). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00371628999710083}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.936622619628906e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999890327453613}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9356848001480103}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8346382975578308}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "HydroRoot", "normalizedForm": "HydroRoot", "offsetStart": 4, "offsetEnd": 13}, "context": "The HydroRoot model was developed in a Python programming language, as a component of the OpenAlea platform (Pradal et al., 2008(Pradal et al., , 2015)).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.2487645149230957}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.06141030788421631}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.5299530029296875e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999890327453613}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9356848001480103}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8346382975578308}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "HydroRoot", "normalizedForm": "HydroRoot", "offsetStart": 12, "offsetEnd": 21}, "context": "The present HydroRoot model proposes to synthetize the overall radial pathway through a single radial conductance (k) value.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.510185241699219e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.4335942268371582}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999890327453613}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9356848001480103}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8346382975578308}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "HydroRoot", "normalizedForm": "HydroRoot", "offsetStart": 14, "offsetEnd": 23}, "context": "Parameters of HydroRoot model.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0009602904319763184}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.5272369384765625e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999890327453613}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9356848001480103}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8346382975578308}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "HydroRoot", "normalizedForm": "HydroRoot", "offsetStart": 21, "offsetEnd": 30}, "context": "Next, we applied the HydroRoot model to calculate the sap flow at a driving pressure of 0.3 MPa [J v (0.3 MPa)] in our collection of simulated RSAs using three distinct, yet realistic hydraulic configurations.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999890327453613}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.005658864974975586}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999890327453613}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9356848001480103}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8346382975578308}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "HydroRoot", "normalizedForm": "HydroRoot", "offsetStart": 22, "offsetEnd": 31}, "context": "In this model, called HydroRoot (https://github.com/openalea/hydroroot), ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00023216009140014648}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.7370873689651489}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8346382975578308}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999890327453613}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9356848001480103}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8346382975578308}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "HydroRoot", "normalizedForm": "HydroRoot", "offsetStart": 25, "offsetEnd": 34}, "context": "The hydraulic aspects of HydroRoot consisted in two main components: the radial water flow between the bathing solution and the xylem vessels and the axial transport through the xylem vessels. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.909247875213623}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003590583801269531}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999890327453613}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9356848001480103}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8346382975578308}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ImageJ", "normalizedForm": "ImageJ", "offsetStart": 26, "offsetEnd": 32}, "context": "Images were analyzed with ImageJ software. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999977350234985}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.125999450683594e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999977350234985}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.125999450683594e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "HydroRoot", "normalizedForm": "HydroRoot", "offsetStart": 27, "offsetEnd": 36}, "context": "Based on these principles, HydroRoot can be run through a two-pass algorithm throughout the RSA, as previously described on aerial branching structures (Prusinkiewicz et al., 2007): equivalent conductances of the different branches are first computed in a backward pass (from root tips to base), followed by a forward pass (from root base to tips) computing the water potentials at each point of the root system. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.4843735098838806}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.800060272216797e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999890327453613}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9356848001480103}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8346382975578308}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "HydroRoot", "normalizedForm": "HydroRoot", "offsetStart": 34, "offsetEnd": 43}, "context": "C.P. supervised the coding of the HydroRoot model and contributed to data analyses.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.21792489290237427}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.07104015350341797}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999890327453613}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9356848001480103}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8346382975578308}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "HydroRoot", "normalizedForm": "HydroRoot", "offsetStart": 34, "offsetEnd": 43}, "context": "Another line of simplification of HydroRoot is that, in most of our simulations, k was set constant from the root tip to base.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9781739115715027}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003368854522705078}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999890327453613}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9356848001480103}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8346382975578308}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SciPy", "normalizedForm": "SciPy", "offsetStart": 46, "offsetEnd": 51}, "context": "We used the function optimize.minimize of the SciPy Python library to perform these minimizations. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999902248382568}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.341934204101562e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999902248382568}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.341934204101562e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "implicit", "software-name": {"rawForm": "programming language", "normalizedForm": "programming language", "offsetStart": 46, "offsetEnd": 66}, "language": {"rawForm": "Python", "normalizedForm": "Python", "wikidataId": "Q28865", "offsetStart": 39, "offsetEnd": 45}, "context": "The HydroRoot model was developed in a Python programming language, as a component of the OpenAlea platform (Pradal et al., 2008(Pradal et al., , 2015)). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.2487645149230957}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.06141030788421631}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.5299530029296875e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.2487645149230957}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.06141030788421631}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.5299530029296875e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "HydroRoot", "normalizedForm": "HydroRoot", "offsetStart": 50, "offsetEnd": 59}, "context": "Thus, we used a parameter adjustment procedure on HydroRoot running with digitized architectures, either intact or with the indicated sections, to infer k (set constant over the overall RSA) and K (as a piecewise linear function of the distance to tip, see \"Materials and methods\").", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999656677246094}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.8133392333984375e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999890327453613}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9356848001480103}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8346382975578308}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "HydroRoot", "normalizedForm": "HydroRoot", "offsetStart": 54, "offsetEnd": 63}, "context": "We then used cut-and-flow experiments assisted by the HydroRoot model developed above to further characterize the hydraulic properties of esk1 roots.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999351501464844}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.10138237476348877}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999890327453613}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9356848001480103}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.8346382975578308}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "implicit", "software-name": {"rawForm": "library", "normalizedForm": "library", "offsetStart": 59, "offsetEnd": 66}, "context": "We used the function optimize.minimize of the SciPy Python library to perform these minimizations. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999902248382568}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.341934204101562e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999902248382568}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.341934204101